agentDot1xPortConfigEntry.description: Represents entry for port config table.

agentDot1xPortControlMode.name: agentDot1xPortControlMode
agentDot1xPortControlMode.description: Dot1x port control mode of this port.The Port control mode . The port control mode for this interface can take the following values , force-unauthorized - the port is in unauthorized mode, auto-Port based mode. If a client authenticates suscessfully, then the interface is authorized . Otherwise, the port is in unauthorized mode. If more than one clients are attached to the port , then only one client needs to authenticate to allow other clients access. force-authorized - The port is placed in authorized mode macBased - If more than one client is attached to the port, then each client needs to authenticate separately. This object depcreates dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl object in IEEE8021-PAE-MIB

agentDot1xGuestVlanId.name: agentDot1xGuestVlanId
agentDot1xGuestVlanId.description: Specifies the Guest Vlan of the port. A port will be moved to its Guest Vlan if no client sucessfully authenticates on that port for the Guest Vlan Period. A value of zero indicates no Guest Vlan is configured for the interface.

agentDot1xGuestVlanPeriod.name: agentDot1xGuestVlanPeriod
agentDot1xGuestVlanPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the guestVlanPeriod constant currently in use for Guest Vlan Assignment for the port .

agentDot1xUnauthenticatedVlan.name: agentDot1xUnauthenticatedVlan
agentDot1xUnauthenticatedVlan.description: Specifies the Unauthenticated Vlan of the port. A port will be moved to its unauthenticated Vlan if the client authenticates unsucessfully on that port . A value of zero indicates no Unauthenticated Vlan is configured for the port.

agentDot1xMaxUsers.name: agentDot1xMaxUsers
agentDot1xMaxUsers.description: Specifies the maximum users or clients that can authenticate on this port when the port control mode is macBased.

agentDot1xPortVlanAssigned.name: agentDot1xPortVlanAssigned
agentDot1xPortVlanAssigned.description: Specifies the vlan the port is assigned to by Dot1x . Only relevant if the port control mode of the port is auto.

agentDot1xPortVlanAssignedReason.name: agentDot1xPortVlanAssignedReason
agentDot1xPortVlanAssignedReason.description: Reason the port is assigned to the vlan specified by agentDot1xPortVlanAssigned . Only relevant if the port control mode of the port is auto.

agentDot1xPortSessionTimeout.name: agentDot1xPortSessionTimeout
agentDot1xPortSessionTimeout.description: Specifies the session timeout value assigned by the Radius server for this port . Only relevant if the port control mode of the port is auto.

agentDot1xPortTerminationAction.name: agentDot1xPortTerminationAction
agentDot1xPortTerminationAction.description: Specifies the session termination action assigned by the Radius Server .This is the action taken when the session times out . Only relevant if the port control mode of the port is auto.

agentDot1xPortMABenabled.name: agentDot1xPortMABenabled
agentDot1xPortMABenabled.description: Specifies if Mac-based bypass authentication is configured for the port.

agentDot1xPortMABenabledOperational.name: agentDot1xPortMABenabledOperational
agentDot1xPortMABenabledOperational.description: Displays the operational value of the Mac-based authentication bypass mode (MAB) on the port.

agentDot1xClientConfigTable.name: agentDot1xClientConfigTable
agentDot1xClientConfigTable.description: A table for dot1x Client details and associated functionality.

agentDot1xClientConfigEntry.name: agentDot1xClientConfigEntry
agentDot1xClientConfigEntry.description: Represents entry for port config table.

agentDot1xClientMacAddress.name: agentDot1xClientMacAddress
agentDot1xClientMacAddress.description: Specifies the client MAC address of the client.

agentDot1xLogicalPort.name: agentDot1xLogicalPort
agentDot1xLogicalPort.description: Specifies the client MAC address of the client .

agentDot1xInterface.name: agentDot1xInterface
agentDot1xInterface.description: Specifies the physical interface to which the client is attached .

agentDot1xClientAuthPAEstate.name: agentDot1xClientAuthPAEstate
agentDot1xClientAuthPAEstate.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine for the client.

agentDot1xClientBackendState.name: agentDot1xClientBackendState
agentDot1xClientBackendState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

agentDot1xClientUserName.name: agentDot1xClientUserName
agentDot1xClientUserName.description: Specifies the username with which the client is authenticated to the Radius server . This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

agentDot1xClientSessionTime.name: agentDot1xClientSessionTime
agentDot1xClientSessionTime.description: Specifies the time elapsed in seconds since the client was authenticated in this session. This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

agentDot1xClientFilterID.name: agentDot1xClientFilterID
agentDot1xClientFilterID.description: Specifies the Filter ID or Diffserv Policy name to be applied to the session . This vlaue is populated only if it has been assigned by the RADIUS server. This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

agentDot1xClientVlanAssigned.name: agentDot1xClientVlanAssigned
agentDot1xClientVlanAssigned.description: Specifies the vlan the client is associated with by Dot1x . This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

agentDot1xClientVlanAssignedReason.name: agentDot1xClientVlanAssignedReason
agentDot1xClientVlanAssignedReason.description: Reason the client is associated to the vlan specified by agentDot1xClientVlanAssigned . This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

agentDot1xClientSessionTimeout.name: agentDot1xClientSessionTimeout
agentDot1xClientSessionTimeout.description: Specifies the session time remaining for the client if assigned by the Radius server . A value of 0 indicates that no session timeout was assigned by the RADIUS server. This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

agentDot1xClientTerminationAction.name: agentDot1xClientTerminationAction
agentDot1xClientTerminationAction.description: Specifies the session termination action assigned by the Radius Server . This is the action taken when the session times out . This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

agentDot1xMonitorModeEnabled.name: agentDot1xMonitorModeEnabled
agentDot1xMonitorModeEnabled.description: Enable/Disable Dot1x Monitor mode Support on the switch.

agentDot1xMonitorModeClients.name: agentDot1xMonitorModeClients
agentDot1xMonitorModeClients.description: Retrieves the number of clients that got authenticated by Monitor mode globally.

agentDot1xNonMonitorModeClients.name: agentDot1xNonMonitorModeClients
agentDot1xNonMonitorModeClients.description: Retrieves the number of clients that are granted access by Dot1x with no monitor mode enabled.

agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultTable.name: agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultTable
agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultTable.description: A table to display the dot1x monitor mode results.

agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultEntry.name: agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultEntry
agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultEntry.description: Represents Dot1x Authentication results for a Dot1x Authentication History table.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfaceIndex.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfaceIndex
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfaceIndex.description: This object represents the physical Bridge Port on which dot1x Auth event might be received.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIndex.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIndex
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIndex.description: Reference to the Dot1x Authentication history table maintained.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultTimeStamp.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultTimeStamp
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultTimeStamp.description: Specifies the exact time of Dot1x Authentication event information occurred maintained in the history table.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAge.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAge
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAge.description: Time since the authentication entry was added to the history table. It is displayed in days, hours, minutes, and seconds.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultMacAddress.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultMacAddress
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultMacAddress.description: Specifies the client MAC Address maintained in the Dot1x Authentication history table.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanId.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanId
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanId.description: Specifies the VLANID maintained in the history table. It is the VLANID which is failed to associate to the port during authentication process. The VLANID is identified distinctly by the Reason code for the respective entry. Valid only when the reason code is set to 13 (VLAN assignment failure). In all the other cases, VLANID is set to 0.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAuthStatus.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAuthStatus
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAuthStatus.description: Specifies the Dot1x Authentication status (Success or Failure) for the Dot1x Authentication event takes place.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAccessStatus.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAccessStatus
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultAccessStatus.description: Authentication access status indicates the exact status of the dot1x client. Granted means the client is allowed access to the network using dot1x or monitor mode. Denied means the client is not allowed access to the network.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultFilterID.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultFilterID
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultFilterID.description: Specifies the Filter ID or Diffserv Policy name assigned by the RADIUS server. This value is only valid when the client is in authenticated state.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssigned.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssigned
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssigned.description: Specifies the VLANID maintained in the history table (It is the VLANID Assigned to a Port or Client authenticate).

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssignedT.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssignedType
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultVlanAssignedT.description: Specifies the VLAN Assigned Reason maintained in the history table.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultReasonCode.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultReasonCode
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultReasonCode.description: Specifies the Dot1x authentication reason refered by the result index on a port.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultsClear.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultsClear
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultsClear.description: When set to enable(1), all Dot1x Authentication History information will be reset.

agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultClearTabl.name: agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultClearTable
agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultClearTabl.description: A table to clear the dot1x monitor mode results per interface.

agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultClearEntr.name: agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultClearEntry
agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultClearEntr.description: Represents to clear the Dot1x Authentication results for a Dot1x Authentication History table.

agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfIndex.name: agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfIndex
agentDot1xAuthHistoryResultIfIndex.description: This object represents the physical Bridge Port on which dot1x Auth event might be received.

agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultsClear.name: agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultsClear
agentDot1xPortAuthHistoryResultsClear.description: When set to enable(1), all Dot1x Authentication History information for the given port will be reset. The value is write-only. Attempt to read will return disable(2).
